{"title_page": "Fran\u00e7ois Bourguignon", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name             = Fran\u00e7ois Bourguignon\n| school_tradition =\n| image       =\n| image_size       =\n| caption    =\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1945|05|22}}\n| birth_place      =\n| death_date       =\n| death_place      =\n| nationality      = [[France|French]]\n| office           = [[World Bank Chief Economist|Chief Economist of the World Bank]]\n| president        = [[James Wolfensohn]]<br>[[Paul Wolfowitz]]\n| term_start       = 2003\n| term_end         = 2007\n| predecessor      = [[Nicholas Stern, Baron Stern of Brentford|Nicholas Stern]]\n| successor        = [[Justin Yifu Lin]]\n}}\n{{Infobox economist\n| institution      = [[Ecole des hautes \u00e9tudes en sciences sociales]]-[[Paris School of Economics]]\n| field            =\n| alma_mater       = [[University of Western Ontario]]\n| doctoral_advisor =\n| doctoral_students = {{Interlanguage link multi|Bernard Salani\u00e9|fr}}\n| contributions    =\n| awards           = [[Dan David Prize]], 2016\n| signature        = <!-- file name only -->\n| repec_prefix     = f\n| repec_id         = pbo225\n}}\n\n'''Fran\u00e7ois Bourguignon''' (born May 22, 1945) is the former [[World Bank Chief Economist|Chief Economist]] (2003\u20132007) of the [[World Bank]]. He has been the Director of the [[Paris School of Economics]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Fran\u00e7ois Bourguignon biography|url=http://econ.worldbank.org/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/EXTDEC/EXTRESEARCH/EXTWDRS/EXTWDR2007/0,,contentMDK:21523993~menuPK:1489857~pagePK:64167689~piPK:64167673~theSitePK:1489834~isCURL:Y,00.html|work=World Bank Website|accessdate=16 January 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110114025806/http://econ.worldbank.org/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/EXTDEC/EXTRESEARCH/EXTWDRS/EXTWDR2007/0,,contentMDK:21523993~menuPK:1489857~pagePK:64167689~piPK:64167673~theSitePK:1489834~isCURL:Y,00.html|archive-date=14 January 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> and from 1985 to his retirement in 2013 a professor of economics at the [[\u00c9cole des Hautes \u00c9tudes en Sciences Sociales]] in Paris.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fran\u00e7ois Bourguignon personal page|url=http://www.pse.ens.fr/bourguignon/index.html|work=Paris School of Economics Website|accessdate=16 January 2011}}</ref> in 2016 Bourguignon was awarded the [[Dan David Prize]].\n\n== Education ==\nTrained as a statistician at [[ENSAE ParisTech|ENSAE Paris]] (French National School of Statistics and Economics), Fran\u00e7ois Bourguignon has a PhD from the [[University of Western Ontario]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Fran\u00e7ois Bourguignon CV |url= http://www.parisschoolofeconomics.eu/docs/bourguignon-francois/resume-bourguignon-francois.pdf |work=Paris School of Economics Website }}</ref>\n\n== Selected publications ==\n\n=== Books ===\n* {{cite book | last1 = Bourguignon | first1 = Fran\u00e7ois | last2 = Atkinson | first2 = Anthony B. | author-link2 = Tony Atkinson | title = Handbook of income distribution | publisher = Elvesier | location = Amsterdam New York | year = 2000 | isbn = 9780444816313 }}\n* {{cite book | last1 = Bourguignon | first1 = Fran\u00e7ois | last2 = Pereira da Silva | first2 = Luiz A. | title = The impact of economic policies on poverty and income distribution: evaluation techniques and tools | publisher = World Bank and Oxford University Press, New York | location = Washington, DC | year = 2003 | isbn = 9780821354919 }}\n* {{cite book | last1 = Bourguignon | first1 = Fran\u00e7ois | last2 = Lustig | first2 = Nora | last3 = Ferreira | first3 = Francisco | author-link2 = Nora Lustig | title = The microeconomics of income distribution dynamics: in East Asia and Latin America | publisher = World Bank Oxford University Press | location = Washington, DC New York | year = 2005 | isbn = 9780821358610 }}\n* {{cite book | last1 = Bourguignon | first1 = Fran\u00e7ois | last2 = Bussolo | first2 = Maurizio | last3 = Pereira da Silva | first3 = Luiz A. | title = The impact of 